2023/08/23</div></section><div><p></p><h2>Buy the Best Laptop Under 50,000 Rupees for You</h2><p><br/></p><p>One of the first things that someone buying a laptop would decide on is the price. A high-end laptop with some of the most advanced features may not be ideal for you if it exceeds your budget. If you&#8217;re looking for a laptop that comes at a reasonable price and includes some of the best features, you can shop online to find some of the best laptops under 50,000 rupees. Brands like HP, Lenovo, Dell and Asus have a range of laptops with useful features that you can have a look at while shopping for laptops under 50,000 rupees online. The following are just a few of the many models that you can have a look at here:&#160;</p><p><br/></p><p><b>Lenovo Yoga 510</b></p><p><br/></p><p>Thin and lightweight with a diamond-cut palmrest, the Lenovo Yoga 510 is easy to carry and comfortable to work on. You can flip, fold, tilt or place it in the standing position to suit the task you are using it for. The laptop has a large battery life that can run for eight hours on a single charge. With the Windows 10 OS, you can enjoy a range of other useful features. The Lenovo Yoga 510 is a good choice for 3D gaming, creative tasks like graphic designing and multitasking, thanks to the 7th Gen Intel Core processor. And you get to enjoy a storage capacity of 512 GB, which means you can store a large number of files on your laptop without the need for an external hard drive.&#160;</p><p><br/></p><p><b>HP Notebook 15-AY009TX</b></p><p><br/></p><p>The HP Notebook 15-AY009TX has a slim design, the Windows 10 OS and the Intel Core i5 processor that makes it a perfect combination of lightness and powerful computing. If you&#8217;re a music lover or movie buff, this can be one of the best laptops under 50,000 rupees for you. You can now enjoy an awesome audio experience with the DTS Studio speakers present.&#160;</p><p><br/></p><p><b>Dell Vostro 3558</b></p><p><br/></p><p>With the Windows 10 Pro OS, the Dell Vostro 3558 promises a smooth and versatile PC experience. The laptop comes with the Intel Core processor, giving you a powerful and efficient performance. You can also enjoy smooth multitasking with 2 GB of discrete graphics. The built-in HD webcam and Waves MaxxAudio technology make the Dell Vostro 3558 one of the best laptops for businessmen who need to make frequent conference calls.</p><p><br/></p><p><b>HP Pavilion x360</b></p><p><br/></p><p>Designed with a 360-degree geared hinge, the HP Pavilion x360 is another laptop that is built for flexibility. You can place it in the stand mode, the tent mode or the tablet mode according to what you&#8217;re using it for. The laptop is also thin and lightweight, so you can carry it anywhere without a second thought. With dual speakers designed in collaboration with the experts at B&amp;O Play and the HP Audio Boost, the laptop lets you hear your favourite tracks with a rich and authentic sound quality.&#160;</p><p><br/></p><p>Choosing the best laptop under 50,000 rupees for you depends on your needs and lifestyle. While a lightweight laptop may be very convenient for someone who travels a lot, a gamer or multitasker may want to buy a laptop with an efficient performance. So, consider the features that are important for you before you shop online to have a look at some of the best laptops under 50,000 rupees for you.</p><h2>Shop for Premium Laptops under 50000 Online</h2><p>Laptops play a huge part in our lives. In [15]:
f = open('laptops_infos.csv', 'wb')
header = "Product_Name,Stars,Rating,Reviews,Current_Price,MRP,Processor,RAM,Storage,Image_URL\n"
f.write(header.encode())

for c in container:
    # finding product Name
    product = c.find('div', {"class": "_4rR01T"})
    Product_Name = product.text.split('-')[0].strip()

    # finding stars
    star = c.find('div', {'class': '_3LWZlK'})
    try:
        Stars = star.text.replace(',','')
    except:
        Stars = '0'

    # finding rating and reviews
    rating = c.find('span', {'class': '_2_R_DZ'})
    try:
        ratrev = rating.text.split('&')
        Rating = ''.join(filter(str.isdigit, ratrev[0])) if ratrev else '0'.replace(',','')
        Reviews = ''.join(filter(str.isdigit, ratrev[1])) if len(ratrev) > 1 else '0'.replace(',','')
    except:
        Rating = '0'
        Reviews = '0'

    # finding current price
    current_price = c.find('div', {'class': '_30jeq3 _1_WHN1'})
    Current_Price = current_price.text.replace(',','').replace('₹','')
    mrp = c.find('div', {'class': '_3I9_wc _27UcVY'})
    try:
        MRP = mrp.text.replace(',','').replace('₹','')
    except:
        MRP = '0'

    # finding information
    info = c.findAll('li', {'class': 'rgWa7D'})
    Processor = info[0].text
    RAM = info[1].text
    Storage = info[3].text

    # finding imgurl
    image = c.img
    Image_URL = image.get('src')
    print(Product_Name,Stars,Rating,Reviews,Current_Price,MRP,Processor,RAM,Storage,Image_URL)
    row = f"{Product_Name},{Stars},{Rating},{Reviews},{Current_Price},{MRP},{Processor},{RAM},{Storage},{Image_URL}\n"
    f.write(row.encode())

f.close()

# Calculate discount
discount= (laptops["MRP"] - laptops["Current_Price"]) 
# Display discounts
#print(discount)
sorted_discount = discount.sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
#print(sorted_discount)
# Create a bar graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sorted_discount.plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Top 10 Laptops with Maximum Discounts')
plt.xlabel('Product_Name')
plt.ylabel('Discount')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Display the graph
plt.show()

In [106]:
# Calculate discount
discount = laptops["MRP"] - laptops["Current_Price"]

# Display discounts
#print(discount)
sorted_discount = discount.sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
#print(sorted_discount)

# Get the product names for the top 10 laptops
top_products = laptops.loc[sorted_discount.index, "Product_Name"]

# Create a bar graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
ax = sorted_discount.plot(kind='bar')
ax.set_xticklabels(top_products, rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.title('Top 10 Laptops with Maximum Discounts')
plt.xlabel('Product_Name')
plt.ylabel('Discount')
plt.tight_layout()

# Display the graph
plt.show()
